19/07/2006
VIENNA, Austria -- Montenegro Foreign Minister Miodrag Vlahovic made his first address to the OSCE Permanent Council on Tuesday (18 July).
He said he expects that an official accord for an OSCE mission in Podgorica to be sealed quickly, and he invited the organisation to monitor the autumn elections.
Vlahovic also praised OSCE's support and contribution to building the newly-independent state.
The country's strategic goals remain full integration in the EU and NATO and contribution to the stability and security in the Balkans, he said.
(Vijesti, Pobjeda - 19/07/06;
Mina, OSCE Web site - 18/07/06)
